The EQAM accepts the following RPC commands from DNCS:

Create Session
> session ID (seems to be picked by DNCS)
  in program number (?, 0 for getting it from PAT)
  out program number
  in port number (?)
  out port number (QAM channel, 8 bit, not enought for entire RFGW!)
  session rate (0 for unknown)
  unicast or multicast
  dest IP addr
  array of src IP addr (up to 3)
  dest UDP port
  pid mapping flag

< result code
  session ID


Delete Session
> session ID

< result code
  session ID


Create Shell Session Group
> out port number
  array of session ID (up to 32)
  group rate

> result code
  array of session status


Delete Shell Session Group
> out port number
  array of session IDs (who assigns these session ID, DNCS or SDV server?)
  (what happens if part of the group is deleted?)

> result code
  array of session status


Query Session
> out port number

< result code
  out port number
  array of session IDs


Query Session Info
> out port number
  session ID

< result code
  in program number
  out program number
  in port number (?)
  out port number
  session rate (0 for unknown)
  in PSI detected
  packets detected
  PMT (in raw format)
  unicast or multicast
  dest IP addr
  array of src IP addr (up to 3)
  dest UDP port
  pid remapping flag


Insert Packet
> array of insert IDs (containing out port number, packet list ID)
  MPEG packet list
  repeat count
  continuous flag
  packet rate
  execution time (supported? how accurate)

> result code


Query Insert Packet
> out port number

> result code
  out port number
  array of insert packet info (?)


Cancel Packet
> insert ID
  cancel all flag

> result code


Reset Indication
(indication is from EQAM to SRM (DNCS), response is from DNCS to SRM)
> MAC address of control port

< result code


